Prompt Engineering :
[x] Read about and practice core prompting techniques: Zero-shot (direct instruction), Few-shot (providing concrete examples of inputs and expected outputs), and Chain-of-Thought (forcing step-by-step reasoning).
[x] Learn how to author robust system prompts that establish a rigid operational persona, explicitly define constraints, and outline edge-case handling rules.
[x] Master the use of structural XML tags (e.g., < context >, < instructions >, < data >) to explicitly separate different blocks of data within your prompt text.
